# bellNumber

- _bellNumber(n)_

Answer the number of ways a set of _n_ elements can be partitioned into nonempty subsets.

There are five ways three numbers can be partitioned:

```
>>> 3.bellNumber
5
```

Threads element-wise over lists (OEIS A000110):

```
>>> 1:11.bellNumber
[
	1 2 5 15 52 203 877
	4140 21147 115975
	678570
]
```

